Christopher Stefanoni says his son was kicked off his team and banned from coaching . 
  He says his affordable housing homes threatened the ethnic makeup of the town of Darien . 
  The town is 94 per cent white and has a median household income of $200,000 . 
  Stefanoni claims his nine-year-old son was moved to a lower team in the Little League because of his housing plans . 
  He was banned from the league and from coaching his son in the league . 
  The property developer says he was demoted because he proposed affordable housing in the town . 
  Darien is a town of 21,000 and has just 70 black residents . 
  Town and Little League deny the allegations . 
 